content.detailedDescription:
My husband gets up to smoke cigarettes at night. he has been observing something in the night sky on and off for about two weeks now. he took three photographs of a bright light above our house with his cell phone about a week ago. he described the light/object as a ufo and says he can see an arm coming out of each side with his naked eye. he has seen two different objects on various occasions, and thinks he may have seen a third but is unsure. he advised me they move too quickly to be easily explained, are too bright to be stars, and do not have any blinking lights to indicate they are airplanes. he has told me that he has watched them remain stationary, move, and change direction. he has said the objects remain in the sky for roughly thirty minutes to an hour when they are there. i can not recall if he has observed them appear or disappear. i am unable to easily identify the object he has taken with his cell phone camera, however the roof of our house is clearly visible and a bright light is visible above it. our house is located around the galleria area of houston, which makes observing stars virtually impossible. the house faces north, with artificial lighting provided by one street lamp on the north side of the house and one theft-deterrent light above the neighboring business to the west. the photos are three consecutive shots facing south with a bright light in the south.

i requested my husband wake me up the next time he saw the objects/lights. on august 25th, 2009 at approximately 4:30am, my husband woke me up to tell me there was one object in the southwest portion of the sky. he advised me to look directly to the right of the building next to our house. he remained inside with our sleeping baby. i went outside and observed a single dot of light in the sky where he indicated. i returned in to confirm with him that this was the object he has been seeing. he advised me that it was. i returned outside with a digital camera and digital video camera. i attempted to capture the object in a series of 18 photographs from 4:51am until 5:06am. the camera had extreme difficulty in automatically focusing on the light even after i changed to a telephoto lens. the digital video camera had difficulty maintaining focus on the light when i zoomed in, as it also has an automatic focus feature. i am unable to adjust the focus for either manually. a second light appeared in the northwestern area of the sky and appeared much smaller and farther away. my husband advised me this was a second object he had also been seeing. i recorded the second object with the digital video camera only.

my husband, myself, and our (now awake) baby all returned inside our house some time after 5:00 am when the baby became fussy. both lights remained visible in the night sky when we returned inside. both objects had moved from their positions significantly since observing their original locations. i would appreciate someone from mufon following up with me on this report so i can submit the photographs and video recording in full. i can provide more comprehensive details of the sighting if necessary, however this report contains the majority. i am hoping the photographs and video footage can be enhanced. more information will be provided to authorized mufon persons upon request.
content.summary: Two unidentified lights in ne and sw locations of early morning sky.

I saw something similar on july 3, 2009!  dark in color a little lighter toward the bottom of it.  the "object" reminded me of an very large x-ray in the sky.  the object was just floating in one place, it looked almost like it was "transparent" in some way, it looked like i was viewing from an reflection from an swimming pool, (if that make sense) another odd thing was, i drove around trying to get a better view of it but for some reason i was not able to.  it should have been visible from a few other advantage points but it was not! (weird)  i first thought maybe it just floated away until i headed back to my home (same route i first noticed it) and there it was again floating in the exact same spot!! (??)   i took off (twice) to see if i could get closer to it and i could only view from one paticular view point. (taking left-hand turn into my subdivision) very strange! i noticed it around 3:40 p.M. and i got home around 4:03 p.M. (judge judy had been on only a few minutes)!

thanks

content.detailedDescription:
I am a private investigator. i was performing a surveillance when i turned onto a street and observed approximately 100 yards in front of, and approximately 500-750 feet above my vehicle, a large object hovering motionless in the sky. 

it was flat and triangular, with rounded corners and sides, and several lights that were yellowish-white, red, blue and green and which were pulsating in no particular pattern. 

i stopped immediately, grabbed my camcorder and exited my vehicle. as soon as i was out of my vehicle, the object darted away at a "bullet-like" speed, and in a southerly direction. as it darted away, all of its lights went out. due to its immediate departure, i was unfortunately unable to obtain any video.

the object was approximately the size of half a football field. its surface appeared to be black or dark gray. it emmited no sounds whatsover. the sky was clear with no light pollution, and countless stars were visible. 

i remained at that location for approximately two additional hours, but did not see the object again.   i am also a licensed pilot and i am familiar with the look of most aircraft. this object looked unlike any aircraft i know and was much larger than any aircraft i have ever seen.
content.summary: Observed large triangular object with pulsating multi-colored lights hovering and departing at very high rate of speed.

content.detailedDescription:
resembled sml white balloon floating around but changed directions several times & then went up & out of sight ! 
   went out for a cig at work and was looking at the hills to the west of chatsworth ca. at about 11.45 am & usually watch planes or helos flying around valley. this object was seen almost directly above my position & high enough that it appeared as small balloon but its flight path was too eractic to be "just carried along w/ wind". it made several circles,then a wide circle , then went up & out of sight.  i understand there have been similar sightings recently in & around this region . maybe it was a balloon, but, i have never seen one behave like that.  by the way, the weather was hot & clear (with probable updraft conditions)altho not windy at 11.00 am.
   this region is rich in sightings from a number of poss reasons. in jan 7th, 2000 i reported (to mufon)a green object that was traveling at incredible speed from n e to s w.  can only speculate how big it was.  now that was a u f o.
   anyway, thanx for listening.
content.summary: Small white light circled above, changed directions & went straight up !

content.detailedDescription:
I was watching tv with my wife when i realized that it was time to start the sprinkler system, almost 7:30pm. it is my routine to do it between 7:30pm and 8:00pm everyday during the summer. even thought the system has an automatic start and end time. i like to manually set it. as i exit the back door, which leads to the back yard, i looked up to the north east, nine o'clock, of the house and saw four objects flying in formation. it reminded me of military planes when flying. i would say about an inch apart when i close my left eye. they were approximately 20 feet above one my next door neighbor���s pine tree. the tree itself stands at approximately 50 feet above ground. i took a good look at them and they seem to be like balloons with candles inside of them. one candle, if you will, per balloon. the balloons were white and translucent. the candle flame stood approximately an inch from the middle bottom of the object. it had the usual bluish, yellow color. it moved very rapidly back and forth. back meaning north east and forward south east. in the same direction the objects were moving. my first impression was that they were balloons with a candle in it. i thought only kids would think of placing a candle inside a balloon and or perhaps a very irresponsible adult. i began to feel agitated and became very concern due to the fact of a fire hazard.
i called my wife and asked her to come to the back door to see the objects. the objects kept on flying at a very slow pace. when they reached the 12:00 o'clock mark right above me. i realized they were not balloons after all but something resembling a jelly-fish shape. the material was white and translucent but not transparent. it seems also organic and biological of some sort.This is the best i can describe it. by this time, my wife had made it were i was standing. she was amazed at the sighting. when the objects reached the 3:00 o'clock mark they began turning left at an approximate 5 to 10 degree angle. as the objects gained altitude and were almost out of sight. the shape changed resembling a red ball like light in the sky. they kept their formation until they gained an incredible amount of speed and went straight up in the air until they disappeared into the south eastern sky.  a few other characteristics i also noticed are that they did not make any noise nor did any smoke came out of the balloon since it was completely sealed at the bottom. 
i stated in the previous paragraph when i first saw them i was astonished but concerned about the possibility of a fire hazard. then, when they passed right above me i had a peaceful feeling. something like time stood still. i thought these objects are beautiful. after they disappear in the sky i got this rush of anxiety to find out what these object were. i had never seen something like this before.
content.summary: Balloons/red lights/jellyfish

content.detailedDescription: Our family, my wife and my two sons,had just come home form a day trip to the upper section of  the clackamas river. we were in the process of cleaning up the car. when all of a sudden our son noah shouts; ufo's! ufo's in the sky! i thought he was kidding since i have told them the story of what had happened the previous week. as i head straight to back yard, i look at the sky and saw five lights flying. as they did before they were flying form the north east going to south east section of the sky. at this time the distance from the house was eastern from the previous week. i asked my son to bring me the video camera and started recording them.
content.summary: Red lights/jellyfish/ballons

content.detailedDescription: I was attending at 6 a.M. exercise class at black rock road park in collegeville, pa (montgomery county).  i ended the class for myself at 6:30 a.M. but the rest of the class continued until 7 a.M.  at 6:30 a.M. i went to my car and put on my shoes to walk on the walking path at the park. as i was walking, i looked to the western sky (maybe south western) and saw a large object hovering in the air.  i thought it was odd since it was not shaped like a hot air balloon.  in stead of being tall vertically as a balloon is it was wide and thin in a horizontal direction.  i kept walking but lost sight of it.  while walking i did see a plane pass overhead (right over the 422 highway) but that looked very different than what i saw.  after i was done with my walk i got in my car, the clock read 6:49 a.M. and left the park.  as i was leaving the park i saw the object again. it seemed to be in the same location as i originally saw it.  that seemed odd to me since i should have been able to see it in that position the entire time i was walking.  it was again not moving.  i stopped and looked for under a minute since there was traffic. it looked long and retangular.  it seemed grey in color.  it was still hovering in the same place that i thought i saw while walking.  i also thought that i saw piers or tower type structure on it but wasn't certain.  it was a little too far away for me to see clearly.  it seemed to be over the towns of mont clair, pa and phoenixville, pa. i turned right out of the park entrance, drove a few feet, turned left into an area that i could park to see if i could observe it again. there were too many trees to see it from that position. i called my husband on my cell phone to tell him what was going on and i looked at the clock in my truck, it read 6:51 a.M. i took route 113 home hoping to be able to see it again since there is less traffic on that road then my normal route home but i didn't see it again.  i also noticed that, at the park,no one else seemed to see it.  but, i was the was the only person on the walking path at the time. this whole experience made me feel really wierd.  i had a paper route for several years where i saw lots of odd things between 2a.M.-7a.M. but never anything that i couldn't logically explain.  this didn't seem like any airplane, hot air balloon, or helicopter that i have ever seen.  the most possible explanation would be a balloon but then why could i not consistently see it in the sky?  i feel foolish submitting this but maybe someone else saw it as well.
content.summary: Spotted retangular object floating in sky that didn't move for several minutes

content.detailedDescription: I received a email from my realtor on a 2.5 acre property that i could get really cheap as in 120,000.00 on a owner contract. i went to see the property outside yelm wa. near mckenna's border. the first shot i took caught me off guard as it looked like a brief look at a leif or bird flying by. when i looked up i only saw sky but the camera saw it. the camera is new andi bought it from fred meyer a week before- sony digital. thinking that was just a bird or leif i went into the mobil that was trashed out and the camera shot even more things. that afternoon i took friends over to the place after showing them the pictures and shot pictures of a bunch of funny round bubble lights that only showed on the camera. our hair on our arms stood on end like static electricity. then to make sure that i didnt have a broken camera, i took shots at home and at the neighbors. the neighbor is a thrston county sherrif who said he too had those bubbles show up on his camera when he checked into buying the same place. needless to say i am not buying that place as too many friends as well as myself were creeped out by all this. if it was a ufo why dont they just make themselves known instead of being so secretive? you would think that with all that technology they would feel a bit safer but no, they just zip in and out. wierd huh?
content.summary: Looking at a piece of property and my digital camera caught it in the sky.

content.detailedDescription: Tonight (august 24th 2009) at 8:10pm my daughter told me there was a bright object in the sky. thinking it was an early star i went outside to look. it was still very light out so i was suprised to see this very bright white object, so i told her it was probably venus or another planet. just to be sure i had brought my binoculars for viewing. i watched this oject for about 15 minutes and it was motionless the whole time then i noticed a west bound commercial plane approaching close to the object so i kept on viewing the object and at one point i could see the object and the plane within the view of my binoculars. the plane appeared to be at cruising alttitude so i'm guessing 30-35,000 feet. the plane didn't react to the object so this further bolstered my belief it was a star or planet. at that moment the object became very fuzzy and dimmer. thinking i had fogged up my binoculars i cleaned the optics and returned to viewing the object. at this point there was a whispy plume coming off of the now dimmer object and within the plume i could see smaller white orbs shooting through. i instantly thought this reminded me of a youtube ufo video from mexico where an object was shooting orbs out of it, i mean it looked almost exactly like that. i ran in to get my video camera and by the time i got back the event was over i swear to everyone who reads this that i actually saw this event as described.
content.summary: As bright as venus then dims while ejecting plume and smaller orbs

content.detailedDescription:
I was driving east on the 52 just two miles east of the 805. i glanced our my driver side window and saw a huge rectangular object in the sky.  it was hovering or moving pretty slowly.  shocking thing was the size of it and the shape of it.  my brain just couldn't compute what it could be, it just didn't belong in the sky.

i wondered could it be something being used at merimar air station for target practice.  it floated like a blimp but a totally different shape and size.  it was rectangular, but almost squar.  it looked like maybe it had a ring around it's middle but i couldn't make out the details.  it was probably a dull grey color similar to a battleship.  i estimated it at about 1 mile (5,000 ft) and moving very slowly.  it was hard to judge the size but i'd guess it was over 300 feet wide and over 200 feet tall.  i think i got a picture on my cell phone camera, but only after it had traveled a ways away.  i might load it on my computer and see if this is what i saw.  did anyone else report this?  i wish someone could tell me what it was.

i was freaked out to say the least.  i called my wife about 5 minutes later and told her what i saw.  i had left my sony hybred camera at home with a 60 power zoom lense.  so the one time i didn't have my camera with me, sure enough, i see something that would of made an incredible picture...
content.summary: Huge rectangular object just north of the 52 and two miles east of the 805

content.detailedDescription:
At the time of the sighting, two adult males (my son and my nephew) and two adult females (my daughter and myself) were walking outside in auburn, washington at 1:39 am as my daughter was going home next door. since we are in a rural location and it was dark out, we were seeing her home safely. she happened to point out that the stars looked different - we are all avid sky watchers - and all looked up to consider what she said. she then said that she had never seen a certain tiny constellation in the southwestern sky and we all looked to the area she was indicating. my nephew asked if it had changed shape, and all four of us noted the change from a 'ladle' shape to a square and then a triangle. stunned, we watched the shape chnage further into a rounded heart shape, a line, a zig zag, and i told my daughter to get her camera which she had left inside my house.

while she was trying to video tape the object, i went into the house, got my camera, and turned all the lights out. i went back outside and we watched and did our best to document what we were seeing.

if the ground were at 0 and directly above us were a 10, the object would have been near the 7. as we stared towards the south south east, the pleiades was at a 9 and to our left (east). at arm's length, it would have taken a nickel to cover it.

at first we thought the lights were shifting into the repeating shapes, but as we watched over 2 hours, we realized it was a saucer shaped object with the lights along the edge and the ship was rotating, causing the light pattern to shift.

the object drifted to the east very slowly, and then drifted back to the west. we could not judge the size very well, but for some reason we all thought it was huge. we watched a sattelite go from the south west to the north east and i would guess that the object was about the same level as it, as the lights were of a similar size. it could have been smaller and much closer - it was impossible to tell.

we also noted several shooting stars, including one that 'shot' slower and did not fade as it curved from the area of the object and went east.

we tried very hard to remain calm, but we all felt a sense of awe and gratitude. we all sent mental messages of  thanks, for what it may have been worth - and we all felt excited and nearly euphoric. we all agreed that what we were seeing was beautiful.

although we took dozens of pictures and videos, which we will gladly send in if requested, the lights were apparently not strong enough to be picked up by our cameras. maybe someone has a program on their computer that can help see what may have been picked up in the videos.

we will continue to sift through them. i am still rather blurry, as i am a bit old for dawn patrol, and i did not actually get to bed until nearly 4:30 in the morning.
content.summary: Amazing saucer shaped ufo with lights that made changing patterns in the sky

content.detailedDescription: My partner and i were working in the yard at 330pm yesterday afternoon.  the day was sunny with a few clouds/pleasant.  we were putting mulch out in the front of the house.  we talked of how low the planes were coming in to dulles from the southwest to the northeast direction.  soon after a 767 rumbled overhead, i noticed 3 black triangular shaped objects that initially i thought were birds.  i mentioned to my partner that the objects were flying too fast for birds, and we noticed that when the objects went in front of a cloud, no flapping of wings were noted.  the 3 objects seemed to be circling around each other, but at the same time, were ascending.  very suddenly, one of the triangular shaped craft simply zipped quickly across the sky, from east to west, very quickly.  i was able to follow the object with the naked eye, but it was very quick--and not a bird.  the other two triangular, dark metal looking objects seemed to still be circling around each other, like a dance.  it was almost like they seemed to be enjoying circling around each other, dancing around the sky.  the other two then followed the same direction as the first, and all turned southward and left our line of sight.  i've been a registered nurse for many years and my partner is career secret service.  we neither one could explain this strange sighting, especially in the flight line of a major airport.  we both mentioned that they were truly unidentified but not sure if they are ours...Or not?  the g forces with the maneuvers alone would be unbelievable with the way the aircraft maneuvered.  it was truly awesome for both of us to see.  again, triangular shaped, somewhat 'chevron' looking, dark metal approximately one to two thousand feet in elevation, and looked about the size of a mid sized sedan...It's difficult to explain this any other way.  i've never reported a sighting because i've really never had one before.  both of us are very objective in our professional and personal lives, but had no explanation for this.
content.summary: 3 metal triangles in dulles flightline

content.detailedDescription:
I was at a friends house, attending a cook out. we were all sitting around talking and having a few cold ones, when we all heard this loud whoosh sound, that got louder and louder. from about 200 yards away, we say four bright red spheres rise out of the brush one by one. the speheres were about the size of a large pickup truck and were glowing a bright red that lit up the surrounding area, including the back of the house we were at. my friends horse all began rearing up and nervously whinnying and runnning around the corral as the objects rose. they all rose quietly into the sky, when the last one got to about 100 feet off the ground they slowly headed off to the east, towards the electric plant that sits outside of monahans. they then seemingly hovered over the plant for about 4 minutes. then they all rose in unison and zoomed off in a near vertical ascent, about 3 seconds later, there was a loud clap of what sounded like thunder, but sounded like a sonic boom. it took about 15 minutes before the animals all calmed down and quiet returned to the countryside.

we all watched in completely and utter amazement, about 1 minute passed by before someone said anything, even then we couldn't come up with a reasonable explanation. alot of us grew up in monahans and many of us have seen the strange glowing lights that seem to be attrated toward the plant, but we've seen them from a long way off, usually at night as we are driving back home from odessa or kermit. they usually are seen only rising up and disappearing into the night sky.

we stayed up most of the night talking about it and we still couldn't come up with an explanation to what we witnessed. but i know that i would have doubted what i would have seen if there had not been 8 other people there with me that night.
content.summary: 4 red glowing spheres

content.detailedDescription:
I was standing on my front porch. the sky was absolutely clear, except for a tiny cloud over the valley. because of that i looked up and watched the 
cloud grow as if it were in a speeded up time frame (very fast). i watched it grow speedily for a few seconds then looked to the side 
(about at 2 o'clock) and saw a tiny round object sitting in the sky. it was white, light gray, or silver. i moved my eyes back to the 
little cloud that was still expanding quickly. a second cloud had sprung to being and was also growing quickly. i reached inside my screen 
door and got my binoculars that i keep there (i'm an avid bird watcher), and looked at the sphere thru them. it had no unusual features even 
seen thru the binoculars, just like a little round ball. i looked back at the clouds, then back at the sphere only to realize it was no longer there. i hadn't seen it leave, 
and don't know where it went. the clouds began to fade and were soon gone, leaving the sky absolutely clear again. i saw nothing further. 
i'm sorry i didn't have time for photos, but i did a quick recreation in photoshop.

linda matusich
content.summary: Sphere near small cloud

content.detailedDescription: I was on the beach with a friend...I pointed out what i believed to be venus....As i looked at some other stars i noticed that they were moving...But not in one direction, but left, right, up down....Etc....I thought about space debris or satellites...But these were not moving across the sky..I saw about 5 or 6 of them...Never have seen anything like it...Could it be explained by atmospheric conditions?...They all pretty much stayed in the same position, but again would move around...My friend noticed them too...Any explanations?...Never lost sight of the "stars"....Just left the beach

content.detailedDescription: While observing the airshow aerial demonstrations, i noted 4 white spherical shaped objects in exact formation (side by side) moving east to west far above the city. the objects were white on the bottom, with some black at the top.  i was able to get a quick glimpse through my binoculars to make sure these were not other planes, or some type of birds.  they were neither.  the objects then vanished.  i contacted the local national weather service office to inquire as to whether they had released any weather balloons, and they had not.  also, when they do release a weather balloon, it is a single balloon, not four. there were two other persons near my location, and when i approached them and asked if they had seen anything unusual, they described the same objects i noted.  these objects were approx 7500 feet up.
content.summary: 4 white globes in formation moving east to west

content.detailedDescription:
I fly as a professional commercial airline pilot for a regional airline.  while flying a salt lake to denver leg in an empty canadair crj-200 regional jet on 22 august, the captain and i witnessed a brilliant bluish white object as we descended through 19000 feet amsl and crossed the "tomsn" intersection in the area of estes park colorado, some 60 miles northwest of the denver international airport.  as we levelled off at 19000 feet, we began slowing from 310 knots indicated to 250 knots indicated airspeed, as instructed by atc.  at this time we noticed a bright white light off to our right (south of us) at about the 3:30 position and apparently the same altitude as us.  it appeared to be another aircraft descending parallel to us into the denver area, but it was extremely bright, appearing as though we were looking directly into its landing lights.  we asked the denver approach controller on 119.30 mhz if he could see any other aircraft off to our right, and he said there were none.  we also had no indication of any aircraft off to our right on our onboard tcas (collision avoidance) system display.  we observed this aircraft (?) from approx 8:07 to 8:09 pm (less than 3 minutes) and it appeared to move eastbound parallel to our course, less than 10 miles off to the right (south) of our position, in the area of longs peak and rocky mountain nat'l. park.  we know it was not a great distance away, since we saw it pass between us and a rain/virga shower in the vicinity of long's peak, off to the right (south) of our track.  it appeared to have at least similar speed to ours (250 to 300 knots), although this is difficult to judge--it seemed to be a bit faster than we were, going eastbound.  as we both began to observe it closely, it literally faded from bright and sharply visible to completely gone in less than three seconds.  it did not appear to accelerate or change course--it just faded rapidly from view and was gone.  another two quick inqiries to the denver approach controller yielded the same answer--he saw neither an aircraft transponder return in that area nor any "primary" return (an aircraft or object simply reflecting radar waves off of its skin).  this was most puzzling to us as we both clearly saw this bright large object and observed it for over two minutes.  it appeared roughly elongate rectangular and very large--perhaps the size of a large jumbo jet(at least 200-300 feet long)...But this is difficult to judge without distance information--i believe it was at least 5 to 8 miles off to our right.  hard to discern surface detail--it simply looked roughly rectangular and extremely bright bluish white light in color (emitting light).  
     i did not have binoculars or a camera with me on this particular flight, so i cannot give much more close detail than this. please feel free to call me with any questions you may have.  i am thinking of requesting the radar tapes from atc.  our flight number was skywest 1008, and we were communicating with denver center on 126.50mhz and then denver approach control on 119.30mhz when the event occurred.
content.summary: Bright bluish white light moving parallel to our aircraft on descent into denver

content.detailedDescription:
I have been out all summer watching space station, shuttle and stars.  went out this night to watch metor shower, saw two.... then something caught my eye, cigar shaped object very high, first i thought it was a search light shinning on some lower thin clouds but realized the object was above the clouds.  outline of object against the stars caused a dark cigar shape moving fast from south to north in a straight line.  i took my eyes off the object to turn around and quickley found it again.  i kept looking at the object, no lights, no sound, just a cigar shape, no wings, nothing else to identify... viewed it for about 6 seconds and lost it from the glare of the city lights.

based on comparison, of stars, space station, metors, planes, etc the object has to be huge. object did not change size, speed or direction. i have seen strange objects but was able to determine and explain...  not this one!!
content.summary: Object was cigar shaped, no lights, no sound, moving fast, south to north in a straight line

content.detailedDescription:
Aug. 19, 2009 13:00
location: archer city, tx
archer city is located near shepperd afb in wichita falls
my spouse and i were on our way to wichita falls. we stopped in at the dairy queen off of hwy 79 in archer city. i was sitting at a booth by a north facing window, sipping on a malt and watching what i assumed was a small white plane. the plane (?) was moving from my ne to ene (west to east) at approx. 5,000 ft agl. it appeared to bank it's wings to the right, then there was a brilliant flash of light which i assumed was a
refection from the sun.  however, at that instant the object took on a diamond like shape. it flew a short distance further and vanished, as if it flew into a hole in the sky. i looked all around that area of the sky and never saw it again. i told my spouse "after the fact", after his having seen the perplexed look on my face. at the time of sighting, my mind was trying to process what i was seeing, so i didn't say anything. my spouse could not see the object, as he was seated facing me and had a wall to his right.  i was facing him, with a clear view out the window, north and east.
i assumed it was a plane, because the object 'appeared' to be a small plane. i should have been able to view the object for quite some distance, as the sky was clear, with just a few puffy clouds. the object was in open sky and not near any of these clouds. i was inside the dairy queen and could not hear any outside noises, except for occasional traffic on hwy 79 and inside the dairy queen. this sighting lasted at most, 10 seconds.
1. having lunch at the dairy queen in archer city.
2. i noticed a small solid white plane headed east.
3. i thought it was a piper cub.
4. the supposed plane was traveling west to east, banked to the right, flashed a brilliant white, then took on a diamond shape.
5. my feeling during sighting was one of wishing i was piloting the plane and after, astonishment.
6.  i lost sight of the object when it simply vanished, like flying into a hole in the sky.

i am sending a depiction of what the object looked like from my perspective (looking through the window at object), just as it began to tilt to the right.
content.summary: I saw what i thought was a plane, that changed into a diamond shape and disappeared.
